ZH: 电线是连接电力的重要设备。
EN: Electric wires are important for transmitting electricity.

ZH: 请小心绕过电线，以免触电。
EN: Please be careful around the electric wires to avoid getting shocked.

ZH: 我们需要检查家里的电线是否有破损。
EN: We need to check if there are any damages to the electric wires in our house.

ZH: 务必确保电线牢固地连接在插头上。
EN: Make sure that the electric wires are securely connected to the plug.

ZH: 在家里安装电线时要遵循安全标准。
EN: Follow safety standards when installing electric wires in your house.

ZH: 风暴过后，电线被吹断了。
EN: The electric wires were blown off during the storm.

ZH: 电线需要定期维护以确保安全使用。
EN: The electric wires need regular maintenance to ensure safety.

ZH: 这根电线已经老化需要立即更换。
EN: This wire is aging and needs to be replaced immediately.

ZH: 电线应该与水管分开放置以避免损坏。
EN: Electric wires should be placed separately from water pipes to avoid damage.

ZH: 他不小心踩在电线上导致被电击。
EN: He accidentally stepped on the electric wire and got shocked.

ZH: 电线被小动物咬断了，导致断电。
EN: The electric wire was bitten by a small animal, causing a power outage.

ZH: 当心不要将电线绞在门框上。
EN: Be careful not to twist the wires around the door frame.

ZH: 修理工认真检查了电线的连接。
EN: The repairman carefully inspected the connection of the wires.

ZH: 漏电可能是电线老化的迹象。
EN: Electrical leakage may be a sign of aging wires.

ZH: 请千万不要随意改动电线连接方式。
EN: Please do not modify the connection of the wires randomly.

ZH: 利用电线悬挂照明设备是不安全的。
EN: It is not safe to hang lighting equipment using electric wires.

ZH: 我们需要将电线整齐地排列在墙角。
EN: We need to arrange the wires neatly in the corner of the wall.

ZH: 电线起火时应该立即断开电源。
EN: The power should be cut off immediately when the wire catches fire.

ZH: 这条电线需要更长一点才能够到插座。
EN: This wire needs to be a little longer to reach the socket.

ZH: 我们正在学习如何正确地布置电线。
EN: We are learning how to properly arrange the wires.
